(344, 'Cryptanalysis of Lee et al.’s authenticated group key agreement', 'uploadFile/48458798-7c18-4807-8e63-02b83a4df45c.pdf', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M6f96419c13b87d8391eed2prod1con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=21&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes', 64, 64, 47, '2012-12-11 06:24:15', '2012-12-11', '1', '2011 International Conference on Advanced in Control Engineering and Information Science, CEIS 2011', '2012-01', 'Authenticated key agreement protocols , Bilinear pairing , Identity-based , Key agreement , Mobile communications , Session key', 'Authenticated key agreement protocols are to authenticate the users who will start a conversation and establish a common session key. In 2009, Cheng-chi Lee et al. proposed a new authenticated group key agreement based on a novel bilinear pairing to provide integrity of the transmitted messages. In this paper, we show that Cheng-chi Lee et al.''s protocol can only ensure the validity between the second step and the third step, and the intermediate message between the first step and the second step can be disturbed by attackers. That is, Cheng-chi Lee et al.''s protocol doesn''t achieve their goal.', 'Authenticated key agreement protocols are to authenticate the users who will start a conversation and establish a common session key. In 2009, Cheng-chi Lee et al. proposed a new authenticated group key agreement based on a novel bilinear pairing to provide integrity of the transmitted messages. In this paper, we show that Cheng-chi Lee et al.''s protocol can only ensure the validity between the second step and the third step, and the intermediate message between the first step and the second step can be disturbed by attackers. That is, Cheng-chi Lee et al.''s protocol doesn''t achieve their goal.', '20115214630973', 1, 1, '', '', '', '2011-08-18', '中国大理', 0.25, 'Yuan Wei, Hu Liang, Li Hongtu, Chu Jianfeng', 't', '63', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M6f96419c13b87d8391eed2prod1con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=21&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes'),
(346, 'A review of the privacy-preserving mechanisms of the smart meter in M2M', 'uploadFile/bb552008-4cb0-491e-8fb9-f254b8853535.pdf', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M7c7eb8b913b87dc5d5a95bprod2con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=1&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes', 64, 64, 41, '2012-12-11 06:53:31', '2012-12-11', '1', 'Journal of Convergence Information Technology', '2012-06', 'Anonymity , Background knowledge , Data informations , Internet of Things (IOT) , K-Anonymity , M2m ', 'The relation between the Internet of things and people is increasingly closed, especially M2M technologies develop rapidly. As one of the most important applications in M2M, the smart meter has been widely spread for its convenience and intelligence. Because the user''s privacy data information is held in smart meter which can be attacked by eavesdropping and tampering, the requirement of privacy-preserving is indispensable. In this paper, after summarizing major privacy-preserving schemes to date, we classify these privacy-preserving schemes as external privacy-preserving schemes and internal privacy-preserving schemes according to the corresponding privacy attacks. The major part of external privacy-preserving schemes is the anonymous data transmission. The k-anonymity, l-anonymity and t-anonymity are proposed to achieve the goal of transmitting data anonymously to resist their corresponding privacy attacks. The internal privacy-preserving schemes involve access control and permission of authentication. Access control gives different users different permission; permission of authentication identifies the user''s permission and resists the force attack. Due to the uncertainty of the background knowledge which is the main attack scheme attackers depend on, we cannot prevent the privacy information from being revealed, namely, there is no perfect scheme to resist all the privacy attacks, existing privacy-preserving schemes are all proposed under a given environment of application.', 'The relation between the Internet of things and people is increasingly closed, especially M2M technologies develop rapidly. As one of the most important applications in M2M, the smart meter has been widely spread for its convenience and intelligence. Because the user''s privacy data information is held in smart meter which can be attacked by eavesdropping and tampering, the requirement of privacy-preserving is indispensable. In this paper, after summarizing major privacy-preserving schemes to date, we classify these privacy-preserving schemes as external privacy-preserving schemes and internal privacy-preserving schemes according to the corresponding privacy attacks. The major part of external privacy-preserving schemes is the anonymous data transmission. The k-anonymity, l-anonymity and t-anonymity are proposed to achieve the goal of transmitting data anonymously to resist their corresponding privacy attacks. The internal privacy-preserving schemes involve access control and permission of authentication. Access control gives different users different permission; permission of authentication identifies the user''s permission and resists the force attack. Due to the uncertainty of the background knowledge which is the main attack scheme attackers depend on, we cannot prevent the privacy information from being revealed, namely, there is no perfect scheme to resist all the privacy attacks, existing privacy-preserving schemes are all proposed under a given environment of application.', '20123215329663', 1, 1, '7', '13', '46-57', NULL, '', 2, 'Chi Ling, Hu Liang, Li Hong-tu, Yuan Wei, Sun Yuyu, Chu Jian-feng', 't', '63', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M7c7eb8b913b87dc5d5a95bprod2con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=1&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes'),
(347, 'A key distribution protocol based on WDH assumption', 'uploadFile/a17d0c19-a7de-4dd7-97ad-738792822c8f.pdf', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M6f96419c13b87d8391eed2prod1con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=16&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes', 64, 15, 47, '2012-12-11 06:58:14', '2012-12-11', '1', '2011 International Conference on Advanced in Control Engineering and Information Science, CEIS 2011', '2012-01', 'Diffie-Hellman assumption, Key distribution , Key-compromise impersonation , Key-distribution protocols ', 'Key distribution is critical for the practicality of any public key cryptosystem and identity-based encryption (IBE) system. When new users register on the PKG, it is important for him/her to obtain his/her private key safely. In this paper, we propose a solution to deal with this problem without smart cards or a third service. We subjoin a user''s private master key using authentication message, by which users can validate the registration information and make sure the security of the protocol based on WDH assumption. We prove that the protocol proposed in this paper can defend the Key Compromise Impersonation (KCI) and Key replicating Attack (KRA). ', 'Key distribution is critical for the practicality of any public key cryptosystem and identity-based encryption (IBE) system. When new users register on the PKG, it is important for him/her to obtain his/her private key safely. In this paper, we propose a solution to deal with this problem without smart cards or a third service. We subjoin a user''s private master key using authentication message, by which users can validate the registration information and make sure the security of the protocol based on WDH assumption. We prove that the protocol proposed in this paper can defend the Key Compromise Impersonation (KCI) and Key replicating Attack (KRA). ', '20115214631026', 1, 1, '', '', '', '2011-08-18', '中国大理', 0.25, 'Li Hongtu , Hu Liang, Yuan Wei, Chu Jianfeng, Li Hongwei', 't', '62', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M6f96419c13b87d8391eed2prod1con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=16&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes'),
(348, 'Improvements against fault induction attack for RC4 algorithm', 'uploadFile/fb1ae3c2-45ab-44c1-a64c-6afa2532deb9.pdf', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M7c7eb8b913b87dc5d5a95bprod2con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=2&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes', 64, 15, 42, '2012-12-11 07:04:02', '2012-12-11', '1', 'Jilin Daxue Xuebao (Gongxueban)', '2012-10', 'Fault induction attack , Line shifts , Non-linear transformations , RC4 algorithm', '由Adi Shamir提出的故障引入攻击是目前破解RC4算法的非常有效的方法,其攻击的目标是RC4的伪随机生成阶段。为了抵抗这种攻击,增加伪随机生成阶段的安全性是十分有效的解决方案。本文提出了两种改进方案,其思想是在原算法的伪随机生成阶段中加入行移位和列移位过程,使其非线性变换更复杂。在对改进算法的正确性、安全性以及使用故障引入攻击破解改进算法的效率进行分析之后,证明了攻击者用故障引入攻击破解RC4算法的效率低于穷举攻击,可以抵抗故障引入攻击。对两种改进算法的效率和安全性进行比较,改进算法1更有效率,改进算法2更安全。 ', 'The Fault Induction Attack (FIA) proposed by Adi Shamir is an effective method in cracking RC4 algorithm. The target of the FIA is the Pseudo-Random Generation (PGR) phase of the RC4 algorithm. To resist this attack, it is necessary to enhance the security of the PGR phase. This paper presents two improvements that make the nonlinear transformation more complex by adding the row shift and column shift to the PGR phase. After analyzing the validity, security and the efficiency of the FIA, it is demonstrated that the efficiency of using FIA is lower than using exhaustive attack, which means that the improvements could resist FIA. Comparison of the two improvements shows that the first improvement is more efficient and the second improvement is more secure.', '20124415623002', 1, 1, '42', '5', '1231-1236', NULL, '', 0.25, 'Hu Liang , Chi Ling, Yuan Wei, Chu Jian-Feng, Xu Xiao-Bo', 't', '63', 'http://www.engineeringvillage.org/controller/servlet/Controller?SEARCHID=M7c7eb8b913b87dc5d5a95bprod2con2&CID=quickSearchDetailedFormat&DOCINDEX=2&database=1&format=quickSearchDetailedFormat&tagscope=&displayPagination=yes'),
